{"id": "44164", 
"title": "Update needed in javadoc for constructor Image(Device , ImageData)", 
"description": "There is a bug in the javadoc for the constructor Image(Device , ImageData). The code snippet below demonstrates the issue:

import org.eclipse.swt.widgets.

public class TestImageInvalidImage {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ImageData data = new ImageData(10, 10, 1, new PaletteData(0xff0000, 0x00ff00, 0x0000ff));
        Image image = new Image(Display.getDefault(), data);
        // image.dispose();
    }
}", 
"OB": "The constructor for Image(Device , ImageData) can also throw org.eclipse.swt.SWTException: Unsupported color depth.", 
"EB": "The javadoc for the constructor Image(Device , ImageData) should be updated to mention that it can throw org.eclipse.swt.SWTException: Unsupported color depth.",
"SR": "Add the information about the potential exception to the javadoc for the constructor Image(Device , ImageData)."}
